In perusing the second part of this volume, the successive stages of Edward’s military progress throughout the country in the year 1296, cannot fail to be regarded as interesting. These stages are not to be completely traced in the acts of homage there recorded; but a more minute detail is to be found in a contemporary document, which has already been printed in the Miscellany of the Bannatyne
